title: ICE triggered by RPITIT function parameter

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I hit an ICE with RPITIT and async_functions_in_trait. ### Code Unfortunately I have no exact repro yet, everything I tried compiles, but some combination triggers the ICE in a larger code base. Hopefully the traces can help track it down. ```Rust // Take the following trait def. // // It has implementers, appears in generic parameters trait Foo { fn foo(&self, val: Option>) -> impl Future + Send + '_; } // It has implementers like: impl Foo for MyFoo { fn foo(&self, val: Option>) -> impl Future + Send + '_ { let val = val.map(Into::into); async move { // ... } } } // The following parameter change triggered the ICE: trait Foo { fn foo(&self, val: Option<&str>) -> impl Future + Send + '_; } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.67.0-nightly (ff8c8dfbe 2022-11-22) binary: rustc commit-hash: ff8c8dfbe66701531e3e5e335c28c544d0fbc945 commit-date: 2022-11-22 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.67.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.4 ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: /rustc/ff8c8dfbe66701531e3e5e335c28c544d0fbc945/compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/visit.rs:103:17: expect tcx.sess.has_errors return true note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.67.0-nightly (ff8c8dfbe 2022-11-22) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib -C embed-bitcode=no -C codegen-units=512 -C debuginfo=2 -C linker=clang -C incremental=[REDACTED] -C link-arg=-fuse-ld=/usr/bin/mold note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: #0 [typeck] type-checking `client::memory::::cancel_task` #1 [thir_body] building THIR for `client::memory::::cancel_task` #2 [mir_built] building MIR for `client::memory::::cancel_task` #3 [unsafety_check_result] unsafety-checking `client::memory::::cancel_task` #4 [mir_const] preparing `client::memory::::cancel_task` for borrow checking #5 [mir_promoted] processing MIR for `client::memory::::cancel_task` #6 [mir_borrowck] borrow-checking `client::memory::::cancel_task` #7 [type_of] computing type of `client::memory::::cancel_task::{opaque#0}` #8 [check_mod_item_types] checking item types in module `client::memory` #9 [analysis] running analysis passes on this crate end of query stack ```
